CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1941, pg. 11, reads: "There is something new under the sun, at least, Eleather Clements in her Broad Street Shop has found it. She gave a manicure party for her patrons last Wednesday which was novel and successful... Top, left: Myrtle Price is getting a manicure by Loretta Runner; a wave by Miss Clements... - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Myrtle Price having manicure by Loretta Runner, and her hair waved by Eleathor Clements, in Clement's Beauty Salon, East Liberty
